The IT department must shrink their budget over time as a percentage of revenue.

Within 5 years the IT budget must not comprise no more than 5 percent of BallotOnline’s annual revenue.

Recommendations must provide a 1 percent reduction in the IT budget as a percentage of revenue annually. 

Hardware capital expenses must depreciate over a 5 year period. 

BallotOnline’s number of physical services and network devices must not exceed 2000, and 10 data centers over a 5 year period in order to support BallotOnline’s infrastructure needs.

A solution must be devised that does not exceed 103.906 GB of storage and 103,906 GB of data transfer in a 5 year period to support BallotOnline’s storage and data transfer needs. 
